    <string name="widget_config_aqi_guide_title">Air Quality Index (AQI) Guide</string>
    <string name="widget_config_aqi_guide_intro">The Air Quality Index is a virtual metric synthesized locally by BoxViewer when a station provides PM2.5 or PM10 particulate matter readings.</string>
    <string name="widget_config_aqi_guide_instantcast">• InstantCast (Live Widget &amp; Dashboard):\nCalculates the index immediately from the latest concentration reading.</string>
    <string name="widget_config_aqi_guide_nowcast">• NowCast (Expanded Card History):\nApplies a 12-hour weighted average algorithm to smooth out temporary spikes.</string>
    <string name="widget_config_aqi_guide_consolidated">• Consolidated Sensor:\nIf both PM2.5 and PM10 exist, it automatically reports the worst-case (maximum) index score.</string>
    <string name="widget_config_aqi_guide_customize">You can customize the regional standard (US EPA, UK DAQI, European EAQI, Canada AQHI, India AQI, China AQI) under the general App Settings.</string>
